SelfBot#

class pynext.SelfBot(token, user_data, http)[source]#

Bases: DiscordUser

Class representing the selfbot object.

Parameters:

  • token (str) – Selfbot token needed to create authorization.

  • user_data (dict[str, Any]) – Date received when logging into the account.

  • http (HTTPClient) – HTTPClient needed to send requests.

gateway#

SelfBot connection to the discord gateway.

Type:

DiscordWebSocket

Type:

State

Method to update selfbot presence.

Parameters:

presence (PresenceBuilder) – PresenceBuilder object.

Raises:

WebsocketNotConnected – Selfbot has not connection to the gateway.

property dm_channels: list[pynext.discord.channel.DMChannel]#

List with dm selfbot channels.

async fetch_dm_channel(channel_id)[source]#

Method to fetch the dm channel by id.

Note

This method will make a api request.

Parameters:

channel_id (int) – Id of the channel we want to get.

Raises:

  • HTTPTimeoutError – Request reached http timeout limit.

  • NotFound – Dm channel not found.

  • Forbidden – Selfbot can’t access that channel.

  • HTTPException – Fetching a channel failed.

Return type:

DMChannel

async fetch_guild(guild_id)[source]#

Method to fetch the guild by id.

Note

This method will make the api request. Consider using get_guild() if you have chunked guilds.

Parameters:

guild_id (int) – Id of the guild we want to get.

Raises:

  • HTTPTimeoutError – Request reached http timeout limit.

  • NotFound – Guild was not found.

  • Forbidden – Selfbot can’t access that guild.

  • HTTPException – Fetching a guild failed.

Return type:

Guild

async fetch_user(user_id)[source]#

Method to fetch the user by id.

Note

This method will make the api request.

Parameters:

user_id (int) – Id of the user we want to get.

Raises:

  • HTTPTimeoutError – Request reached http timeout limit.

  • NotFound – User not found.

  • Forbidden – Selfbot can’t access that user.

  • HTTPException – Fetching a user failed.

Return type:

DiscordUser

property guilds: list[pynext.discord.guild.Guild]#

List of servers on which selfbot is available.

Note

If chunk_guilds in the PynextClient is set to False, the list will be empty.

You can call the fetch_guild() method to fetch guild object.

property http: HTTPClient#

Returns the global HTTPClient.

is_ready()[source]#

Whether selfbot is ready.

Return type:

bool

property latency: float#

Websocket latency value. (Multiply by 1000 to get the value in milliseconds). Contain a value 0.0 if the websocket is not yet connected or didn’t receive HEARTBEAT_ACK.

property token: str#

Selfbot authorization token.

property users: list[pynext.discord.discorduser.DiscordUser]#

A list of discord users that the selfbot has access to.

property voice_states: dict[pynext.discord.guild.Guild, pynext.discord.channel.VoiceChannel]#

Voice states the selfbot is on.
